Ref. no : C/VOU/OFF(SUPP)/11/21-AP2
 
Major Duties:
(a)
      To administer procurement operations including issue and acceptance of purchase orders / tenders, sourcing, contract monitoring, orders / tenders and contract negotiations;
(b)     To assist and coordinate Supplies team to ensure efficient and effective supplies service deliveries;
(c)
      To supervise subordinates for provision of quality, professional procurement and supplies services, including integrity and ethics;
(d)     To offer professional advice / guidance to users on procurement and supplies matters;
(e)     To implement procurement policies, and conduct periodic review where necessary;
(f)     To help maintain operations of computerised procurement and supplies systems effectively;
(g)     To coordinate stock-taking and supervise the data maintenance of the inventory management system; and
(h)     To assist in development and implementation of projects as assigned.
 
Requirements:
(a)
      A recognised degree preferably in Purchasing and Supply Management, Supply Chain Management, Business Administration or equivalent;
(b)     At least two years’ relevant work experience, preferably in sizeable or comparable organisations;
(c)     Proficiency in Microsoft Office Software and computerised accounting / purchasing systems;
(d)     Good negotiation, problem-solving, time management, interpersonal and communication skills;
(e)     Good team spirit, be proactive and able to work independently under pressure; and
(f)     Good command of English and Chinese.
 
Notes:
(1)     Shortlisted candidates may be required to attend a written test in English.
(2)     The appointee may be required to perform duties outside normal office hours and in designated places as assigned.

Application Procedures:
A completed application form [VTC-1 (Rev. 1/2018)], together with a full curriculum vitae, should be sent to the Human Resources Division, 18/F, VTC Tower, 27 Wood Road, Wanchai, Hong Kong.  Please specify on the envelope the reference of the post being applied for.
 
Closing date for application: 7 February 2022

 Applicants not invited for interview within 10 weeks from the closing date may consider their applications unsuccessful.
 
The Council reserves the right not to fill the post(s).
 
Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only. Information on unsuccessful candidates will normally be destroyed 12 months after the completion of the recruitment exercise.

[Steam A: Certified WSET Level 3-4 student, English Speaking, plus Native Cantonese]
[Steam B: Global Food Sourcing + 3 years or above stated/lived in Europe]
[Steam C: Certified WSET Level 1-2 student, Frozen Food Sourcing, English Speaking, plus Native Cantonese]
 
Main Duties:
Develop table wine and spirits products, relevant frozen meat and seafood;
Assess the quality of wine, sales and promotion planning, storage and logistic support, etc;
Able to provide suggestion on food pairing with wine tasting;
Meet overseas suppliers(Occasionally contact suppliers during overseas time zone);
Travel to overseas(US, UK, Northern Europe, India, Southeast Asia, Australia, etc),source and audit new suppliers;
Handle price negotiation in local market, cost comparison & analysis;
Maintain weekly price update and promotion programs;
Able to host, provide guiding and training to colleagues in internal wine tasting event;
Important: Instead of related experience in the field, good intuitive and common senses are overwhelmingly important requirements for the above position. Candidate with multi-language skill is highly preferred (i.e. Good command in 3 or more languages: English / Mandarin / Japanese / Korean / etc.)

Other duties of the above position are:
Act as a sourcing & general support officer in purchasing department;
Handle sourcing, price negotiation, payment terms, PO, Shipping Documents, order follow up as well as payment arrangement , etc;
Communicate between with suppliers and production teams;
Maintain current product supply and ensure in stable quality;
Liaise with factories for production schedule & quality checking;
Handle shipping Documents, Delivery Control;
Internal communication with warehouse for stock management, food quality control, etc;
 
Requirements:
2-5 years' work experience, preferably in sales or trading, purchasing office, food industry;
Holder of driving license (Hong Kong and IDP)
Degree holder, preferably in Business administration, supply chain, food science disciplines;
English typing speed 40wpm is a must;
Good written and spoken English;
In-depth knowledge in EXCEL spreadsheet; with ERP experience, data analytic skill;
Able to work multi-tasks under pressure and deliver on schedule;
Self-motivated, positive, energetic and keen on learning;
Be honest, loyal;
Good adaptability to different and fast-changing company/procurement policies is a plus;
Strong team player and communicator;
Disciplinary, punctual.
We offer 5-day work, Free lunch, Monthly incentive, 12 days annual leave, Birthday leave, 10 days paternity leave, Employee purchase discount, Medical insurance and Annual body check to the above position.
 
Interested parties please send Full resume to HK JEBN LIMITED, including the following details:
 
1)     Availability
2)     Expected salary
3)     Present salary

*HK JEBN Group policies on non-recruitment of smokers or other tobacco users.
 
All personal data collected will be treated in strict confidential and be used for recruitment purpose solely.

Responsibilities:

Responsible for outdoor apparel, footwear and accessories buy;
Handle annual / seasonal buying process from budgeting to launching;
Formulate buying strategies, develop OTB plans and product mix allocation to optimize sales plan and gross margin;
Regularly keep track of sales trend to provide relevant strategies accomplishing business objectives;
Responsible for shipment and order follow up;
Handle full set I/E documents independently;
Liaise and coordinate internally and externally on shipping / local transportation;
Prepare packing list, invoice and delivery note;
Communicate with China headquarter and forwarding company for shipment arrangement;
Analyze the data to formulate a right product plan and solutions to fit for the business needs and cater for the market trend;
Conduct and analyze regular buying and selling related report;
Shop visit and regular travel for trade shows are required.

Requirements:

A Bachelor's degree in related disciplines is preferred;
Minimum 2-3 years’ of solid outdoor sports buying experience including planning & budgeting;
Working experience in I/E firm or shipping related company is preferred;
Strong fashion sense, detail-oriented with good analytical and reporting skills;
Energetic, proactive, self-motivated, able to work independently and meet tight deadline;
Good team player with strong sense of responsibility;
Proficient in MS Word and Excel;
Good command of written and spoken Chinese and English;
Occasional travel is required;
Immediate available is highly preferable.

Responsibilities:

Responsible for procurement activities including sourcing, price and terms negotiation with suppliers, order follow up;
Monitor the inventory level and prepare stock forecasting;
Conduct regular vendors’ evaluation and assessment;
Deal with quality complaints;
Maintain supplier databases and purchase records;
Prepare cost comparison to assist decision making;
Coordinate with internal teams to achieve smooth operation process;
Ad hoc assignments.

Requirements:

Diploma or above in Procurement, Supply Chain Management or related discipline;
At least 2 years of work experience in procurement and sourcing preferably in food trading;
Fresh graduates are also welcome;
Candidate with less experience will be considered as Assistant Purchasing Officer;
Good command of spoken and written Chinese (both Cantonese & Mandarin) and English;
Proficient in MS office applications;
Self-motivated, well-organized with excellent analytical and negotiation skills;
Immediate availability will be an advantage.

We offer competitive remuneration and fringe benefits including discretionary bonus, medical insurance, annual leave and 5-day workweek. Interested party please send detailed resume in both Chinese and English version with expected salary & date of availability by clicking "Apply Now".

Personal data will be used for recruitment purpose only.

